            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>when they appointed him as their member of the<lb/>
                <add>Hebrew</add> put him forth as their religious chief.<lb/> I should say no other
                conclusion can be drawn<lb/> from their act but that they did do so.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">KKBenai Israel has no clique, has no jealous<lb/> feelings, “judge
                not lest ye be judged” KKB Israel<lb/> has a reader who for 18 years have
                    <sic>sewed</sic> them they<lb/> will not dismiss him even with the progress of
                the<lb/> age, how many ministers have Benai Jeshurun<lb/> had? Who is the clique
                that first engages and then<lb/> rejects? or are they so constituted that the
                minis<lb/>ter can not remain with them, all these questions<lb/> become pertinent
                when the <hi rend="underline">representatives</hi> of one<lb/> Congn because members
                of another write certain<lb/> matters attack the Congn of which those
                    <del>gentlemen</del><lb/> writers are members. Have the KKB Israel ever<lb/>
                missed in these disputes? if not why attack her or<lb/> attempt to bring her into
                controversy, all such <sic>attemps</sic><lb/> are futile, and will be, she rests too
                well on her<lb/> duties without engendering or aiding quarrels, why<lb/> is her
                clerical head traduced by <sic>inuendo</sic> or by direct<lb/> charge. Amongst the
                multitudinous<lb/> and multifarious matters in that delectable ema<lb/>nation in
                your <date>April</date> number it is said that “the Par<lb/>-nas knowing
                    <persName>Mr Malzer</persName> to be the dictator of the Congn “&amp;c<lb/>
                <del>that</del> which sentence conveys two erroneous charges first that the
                Par<lb/>nas knew a fact and second that that fact exis=<lb/>ted, as it is not true
                that <persName>Mr Malzer</persName> is or ever was<lb/> the dictator of the congn
                both those statements are<lb/> unfounded, and how knew those gentlemen what
                    <persName>Malzer</persName><lb/> fears, or his motives were, Oh charitable men,
                to<lb/> ascribe baseness where the Immaculate along can<lb/> judge. The writer or
                rather the signer<lb/> of the paper to which I have already referred<lb/> appear to
                have had the idea that they will kill three<lb/> birds with one stone first
                    <sic>annihalate</sic>
                <persName>Malzer</persName> and</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p><persName>Myer</persName>, next disparage KKB <del>Jeshurun</del> Israel and
                thirdly<lb/> to lavish on themselves (their congn) all praise<lb/> modest gentlemen,
                wise gentlemen and just gentlemen.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Wherefore seek to widen a breach if any<lb/> does exist between the
                KKBI &amp; the KKBJ do<lb/> not all the attributes of religion and of the
                    <sic>Diety</sic><lb/> teach, a contrary course. I claim again that<lb/> so far
                as our Congregation as a whole is concer<lb/>ned there is no “jealous feeling
                manifested” on the<lb/> contrary we have endeavoured to <sic>harmonise</sic>,
                to<lb/> united in the progress of Judaism, we have endea<lb/>voured to have a common
                burial ground, we were<lb/> met with a declination, we desired to have a United
                School for the two Congns and in reply we<lb/> were met by the passage of the
                following resolutions<lb/> by the whole Congregation of KKB Jeshurun in<lb/>
                <date>March 1850</date> “Whereas we have Read a communica<lb/> “tion from our sister
                congregation KKBna Israel<lb/> “in which they show their <hi rend="underline"
                    >unanimous</hi> favor in<lb/> “this projected <hi rend="underline">Union</hi>
                Whereas at the present<lb/> “the Congregation KKBeni Jeshurun have established<lb/>
                “the Talmud Yalodim School which is in a most<lb/> “prosperous condition and whereas
                This congrega<lb/> “=tion fearing from what has heretofore passed be<lb/> “=tween
                them different congregations can see at<lb/> “present no advantage by uniting with
                Congn<lb/> “B Israel” Here is their spirit and still<lb/>they as representatives of
                KKB Jeshurun charge<lb/> KKB. Israel with manifesting adverse and jea<lb/>lous
                feelings. I could Sir increase<lb/> proofs and arguments I desist because I do
                not<lb/> desire to mix myself up in this cauldron my<lb/> chief aim has been to
                deny, what by implica<lb/>tion I have been charged with that is mixing in<lb/> this
                matter heretofore. I have cautiously<lb/> abstained from commenting at all on
                Revd</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p><persName>Mr Rosenfelt</persName>, the charges brought against him, or<lb/> the
                theological discussion, I have also endea-<lb/>voured in the explanation I have seen
                fit to make<lb/> to abstain from <sic>offence</sic> to any individual or to<lb/> the
                KKBI if I have done either it is without<lb/> intent. In conclusion I am</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">Joseph Abraham</persName>
            </p>
